# Project Structure

EcoDeli is a Next.js application that provides a platform for eco-friendly delivery services connecting clients, delivery personnel, merchants, and service providers.

## Directory Structure

### App Router Structure
- `src/app/` - Next.js App Router pages and API routes
  - `(auth)/` - Authentication-related pages (login, register, etc.)
  - `(dashboard)/` - Dashboard pages for different user types
  - `(public)/` - Public-facing pages (home, about, etc.)
  - `api/` - API endpoints for the application

### Components and UI
- `src/components/` - Reusable React components
  - `auth/` - Authentication-related components
  - `dashboard/` - Dashboard-specific components
  - `layout/` - Layout components (navigation, etc.)
  - `ui/` - UI components (buttons, forms, etc.)
  - `providers/` - Context providers

### Data and State Management
- `src/lib/` - Utility functions and services
- `src/services/` - Service layer for API communication
- `src/hooks/` - Custom React hooks
- `src/schemas/` - Validation schemas (Zod)
- `prisma/` - Database schema and migrations using Prisma ORM

## Key Files
- `prisma/schema.prisma` - Database schema definition
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Root layout component
- `src/app/page.tsx` - Homepage component
- `package.json` - Project dependencies and scripts